Capstone Exercise: Build a Complete Prompt

Scenario
A training organization has collected feedback from 100 learners after a project management course. Management wants to understand satisfaction levels, major concerns and improvement priorities.
Learner Task
Create a prompt that instructs ChatGPT to:
Act as a training quality analyst.
Analyze the supplied learner feedback.
Group the feedback into themes.
Classify each theme as Positive, Negative or Mixed.
Identify frequency and business impact.
Include representative comments.
Recommend corrective actions.
Avoid inventing data.
Return the result in a structured table.
Finish with an executive summary of no more than 150 words.




Capstone Exercise: Build a Complete Prompt: Solution

Sample Prompt
Act as a training quality analyst. Analyze the learner feedback provided between <feedback> and </feedback>. Group similar comments into meaningful themes. For each theme, identify the sentiment as Positive, Negative or Mixed, calculate the number of related comments, describe the potential business impact and recommend a practical corrective action. Include one representative comment from the supplied feedback for each theme.
Present the analysis in a table with the columns Theme, Sentiment, Comment Count, Representative Comment, Business Impact and Recommended Action. Do not invent comments or statistics. If the available feedback is insufficient to support a conclusion, state this clearly.
After the table, provide an executive summary of no more than 150 words covering the three most important findings and actions.
